SIMPLE: superfluity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Superfluity
<hw>Su`per*flu"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Superfluities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>superfluit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, L. <ets>superfluitas</ets>. See
<er>Superfluous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A greater quantity than is
wanted; superabundance; <as>as, a <ex>superfluity</ex> of water; a
<ex>superfluity</ex> of wealth.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A quiet mediocrity is still to be preferred before a troubled
<qex>superfluity</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Suckling.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state or quality of being superfluous;
excess.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧By a <xex>superfluity</xex> abominable.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Something beyond what is needed; something which
serves for show or luxury.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Superabundance; excess; redundancy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Superfluous</ent>⟦br⟧
